spanGrp.span: This story is called 'The group of children.' A group of ten kids.
Naferkal is a group of children who are at one place and they call them Naferkal.
§ 035-002 Naferkal ga taos ipi teesa , teesa laap rutu naor iskei kin rusosor kir Naferkal .
This group of ten were there and then they made a garden, they planted everything, cabbage, taro, yam.
§ 035-004 Naferkal ralim iskei ruto panpan go ruto preg talm̃at rulao sernale , rulao nafnag , altuk , ntal , nawi .
They were there and they looked to the sea and saw a big boat coming.
§ 035-005 Ale runa ruto panpan go rupam̃or , rule pak elau go rupam̃or raru p̃ur iskei imai .
A big boat came. It came and anchored. Ok, they went down to the sea.
They went down to the sea, and they bought, some bought axes and some bought knives, some bought shovels and picks, things for the garden.
§ 035-007 Runa rusu pak elau , go runa rupaakot , rupaakot , tete rupaakot kram tete rupaakot masmes , tete rupaakot safel , pik sernale nig talm̃at .
Then a small child, the last child bought a mouth organ for them to blow, a mouth organ, he bought it.
§ 035-008 Panpan me teesa sees , tenen ipi takrik ga ipaakot ga nalag nen ruto si , mouthorgan , ga ipaaktofi .
Then they went to work in the garden, and the big ones made the garden, and planted things. But the small one stayed and played his mouth organ.
§ 035-009 Ale malen rupan na rukfreg talm̃at go tep̃afp̃of rupreg talm̃at rulao
sernale . Me tesees ne ga ito me ito si nalag .
He blew on the mouth organ, and there was a big banyan tree there. There was a devil living in the trunk of the banyan.
§ 035-010 Ito si nalag ga ne , panpan me ipiatlak nlak mpak p̃ur
iskei me ito . Nlak mpak ipiatlak ntwam iskei ito em̃rom nlak mpak .
§ 035-011 Teesa sees nen ina ito si nalag , go ntwam nen inrog wi ki nalag .
The child kept on playing a song, and the devil heard it and liked it. He liked the song and he came out closer and then
he came to look at the child and he said, "I feel good hearing your song. Try and blow it again." And the small child kept blowing a tune. The devil liked hearing it. Then he said,
Ina inrog wi ki nalag go ito mai , ito
nrus mai pak m̃eltig , panpanpan § 035-012 imai na
ilek teesa sees ne go ina , " Atrau nrog
wi nalag gaag . P̃amer pregnrogo si ." Me teesa
sees imer si nalag . Ntwam inrog wi ki .
"Give it to me so I can try your mouth organ." The devil took it to blow it, but he ran away. He took it and ran inside the banyan.
kapregnrogo gaag si ." Ntwam ina isat
nalag na isi , trau sati sef .
Isati sef pan ale isil mpak .
§ 035-014 Ale teesa sees nen ito kai . Ikai panpan go tep̃afp̃of
runa ruto rumai pauski na , " Iku kin kuto kai ?"
Then the small child cried. He cried until the adults came and asked him, "Why are you crying?" And,
"The devil in the banyan came and took my mouth organ, and ran away."
Go , § 035-015 " Ntwam ito nlak mpak ina
imai isat nalag neu sef me pa kipe ."
So all the children went to hit the devil, but the devil was inside the banyan, so they dug its roots.
§ 035-016 Ale teesa nen runa ruto rupan stat , runa rukwat ntwam , me ntwam isil to mpak , ale rutraf rutraf nako mpak .
Some cut it with axes, some dug with picks, on and on but it wouldn't fall down.
§ 035-017 Tete rutai ki kram , tete rukili ki pik , panpan mpak nen ikano tarp̃ek .
They dug more and then sang,
§ 035-018 Runa rutraf sees kaimer lag runa , §
[song] Napag imarie rie, napag imarie napag imarie rie, napag inawe,
035-019 " Napag imarie rie , napag imarie napag imarie rie ,
napag inawe , § 035-020 nawe , nawe nau tagisi ."
§ 035-021 Ale inom go ruimer ruimer pregnrogo mpak ruimer ne nri .
Finished, and they tried again to dig out this banyan. They dug it again and again, but it wouldn't fall down, so they sang again:
[song] Napag imarie rie, napag imarie napag imarie rie, napag inawe, nawe, nawe nau tagisi.
Ruimer nri , me mpak ikano tarp̃ek , ale ruimer lag , § 035-022 " Napag imarie rie , napag
imarie napag imarie rie , napag inawe , nawe mpak , me nawe rumer nau nri tagisi mpak ."
But the banyan would not fall over. The small boy decided to go and cut a digging stick, made of cabbage plant.
§ 035-023 Me mpak ikano tarp̃ek ale runa ruto . Ale teesa seesp̃al
ne ina ito kin ipo pan tai kaal iskei , kaal altuk .
So he cut the cabbage digging stick. The big children said, "But this digging stick is soft."
§ 035-024 Ale itai kaal altuk iskei . Teesa p̃afp̃of
runa , " Me kaal go ina imailumlum ."

We tried with a big digging stick, but we couldn't dig the banyan. You brought a digging stick made of cabbage tree, it is too weak and you will try to dig the banyan with it. And he said, "I'll try." And they sang for him:
§ 035-025 Komam upregnrogo ki kaal p̃afp̃of me ukano nri mpak
. Me ag kusat kaal nen ipi altuk imailumlum go kupo
na p̃anri mpak ki . Me ina , " Kapregnrogo ."
[song] Napag imarie rie, napag imarie rie, napag inawe, nawe, nawe nau tagisi.
Ale rupo ga lag , § 035-026 " Napag imarie rie , napag
imarie rie , napag inawe , nawe , nawe nau tagisi ."
So he dug with the cabbage digging stick, he dug, and the banyan fell over.
§ 035-027 Ale ina ilaoki kaal altuk ga , ina inri go mpak itarp̃ek .
The banyan fell over. Then the devil left and they held him and they cut his throat.
itaf ale rupuetsok ntwam ale rutai kot nanuen .
